author: Adam Jude
title: Huskies’ Oct. 17 home game vs. Oregon set for a late kickoff
text:
Huskies’ Oct. 17 home game vs. Oregon set for a late kickoff Originally published October 5, 2015 at 10:23 am The new Husky Stadium was unveiled in September 2013. (Alan Berner/The Seattle Times, 2013) Game to air on ESPN or ESPN2. By Adam Jude Seattle Times staff reporter 
Washington’s Oct. 17 home game against rival Oregon has been scheduled for a 7:30 p.m. kickoff, the Pac-12 announced Monday. It will be the first night game of the season at Husky Stadium. 
The game will air on either ESPN or ESPN2. 
The Huskies travel to Los Angeles for a 6 p.m. kickoff Thursday against USC for an ESPN broadcast. Adam Jude : 206-464-2364 or ajude@seattletimes.com ; on Twitter: @A_Jude . Adam Jude is the UW football beat writer for The Seattle Times.
